formatDescription: MATLAB (an abbreviation of MATrix LABoratory) software and language enables the user to undertake numerical computation and visualization, programme and analyze data, develop algorithms, and create models. Files with extension m are the source code that executes MATLAB commands. A single MATLAB simulation can contain multiple .m files, each one performing a different function.
